{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sabah", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Sabah, Malaysia}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in Sabah\n| width           =\n| image           =\n| image_size      =\n| image_upright   =\n| alt             =\n| caption         =\n| map1            =\n| legend1         =\n| map2            =\n| legend2         =\n| map3            =\n| legend3         =\n| map4            =\n| legend4         =\n| map5            =\n| legend5         =\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Sabah]], Malaysia\n| first_case      =\n| arrival_date    = 12 March 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=03|day1=12|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| date            = \n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| confirmed_cases = 285\n| suspected_cases =\n| severe_cases    =\n| recovery_cases  = 125\n| deaths          = 4\n| territories     = 17/26\n| total_ili       =\n| website         = {{URL|http://covid19.sabah.digital/covid19}}\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Sabah]], [[Malaysia]], in March 2020.\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\"\n|+{{nowrap|Distribution of cumulative confirmed cases in districts of Sabah (As of 15 April 2020)}}\n! colspan=\"2\"| [[Districts of Malaysia#Sabah|Districts]]\n! Confirmed\n! Recovered\n! Deceased\n! Active\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Beaufort District|Beaufort]]\n| 10\n| 5\n| 0\n| 5\n|-\n| 2\n| [[Keningau District|Keningau]]\n| 11\n| 0\n| 0\n| 11\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Kinabatangan District|Kinabatangan]]\n| 19\n| 16\n| 0\n| 3\n|-\n| 4\n| [[Kota Belud District|Kota Belud]]\n| 5\n| 4\n| 0\n| 1\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Kota Kinabalu District|Kota Kinabalu]]\n| 40\n| 18\n| 2\n| 20\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Kunak District|Kunak]]\n| 8\n| 4\n| 0\n| 4\n|-