[Village development committee (Nepal)|village development committee]] in [[Rautahat District]] in the [[Narayani Zone]] of south-eastern [[Nepal]]. At the time of the [[1991 Nepal census]] it had a population of 3503 people living in 637 individual households.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/nepalcensus/form.php?selection=1|title=Nepal Census 2001|work=Nepal's Village Development Committees|publisher=[[Digital Himalaya]]|accessdate=29 November 2008 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Rautahat District}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Rautahat District]]\n\n\n{{Narayani-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Pegship", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2013{{Narayani-geo-stub}}, +{{Province2NP-geo-stub}} usingStubSorter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tengraha"}
